BT /F1 24 Tf 50 700 Td (Chapter 2: The Habit Loop) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 660 Td (The process of building a habit can be divided into four simple steps: cue, craving,) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 640 Td (response, and reward. First there is the cue. The cue triggers your brain to initiate) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 620 Td (a behavior. Cravings are the second step. They are the motivational force behind every) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 580 Td (habit. The third step is the response. The response is the actual habit you perform.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 560 Td (Finally rewards are the end goal of every habit. The cue notices the reward. The craving) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 50 540 Td (wants the reward. The response obtains the reward.) Tj ET
